rs.\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He participated in the African Tournament in Johannesburg, where was ranked the fourth best speaker (The three man team of CHAAPA was ranked number FIVE).\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 498, \"end\": 510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\", \"score\": 0.9999194235366694, \"rank\": 2.9061136438852395e-05, \"text\": \"Johannesburg\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elvin was elected unopposed as Head Prefect because of his outstanding debate skills and clear discipline record.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Head_girl_and_head_boy\", \"score\": 0.9999947745994959, \"rank\": 5.225427759694215e-06, \"text\": \"Head Prefect\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Head_girl_and_head_boy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Head_girl_and_head_boy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In all these undertakings, Elvin has been supported by the school, including offering him extra time for his academic work at school.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This time round, Elvin needs wider recognition and support as he treads the platform of Global Debate in Greece.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9451627846301371, \"rank\": 0.056566848862225, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From our history, other debators at world tournament include: Chris Nkwasiibwe who debated in Vlissingen, Netherlands in 2010 ( Led by the current Head Master , then as Debate Patron) and Onesmus Mwesigwa a former Head Prefect in 2011, in Istanbul, Turkey.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1067, \"end\": 1077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vlissingen\", \"score\": 0.9999999996160795, \"rank\": 3.25042331762354e-10, \"text\": \"Vlissingen\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vlissingen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vlissingen\"}, {\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.8918194077666315, \"rank\": 0.11266145613861396, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"score\": 0.9983093272447443, \"rank\": 0.0012539885525096807, \"text\": \"Istanbul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\"}, {\"begin\": 1222, \"end\": 1228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.87764935137367, \"rank\": 0.13429061631815942, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"editor  See author's posts\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1257, \"entities\": []}]}"